ring. It is defined such that `𝓕.normalOrderRel φ₀ φ₁`\nis true if one of the following is true\n- `φ₀` is a field creation operator\n- `φ₁` is a field annihilation operator.\n\nThus, colloquially `𝓕.normalOrderRel φ₀ φ₁` says the creation operators are less than\nannihilation operators. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/NormalOrder.html#FieldSpecification.normalOrderRel","kind":"def","line":17,"name":"FieldSpecification.normalOrderRel","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L17-L26"}}],"imports":["Init","PhysLean.QFT.PerturbationTheory.FieldSpecification.Filters","PhysLean.QFT.PerturbationTheory.Koszul.KoszulSign"],"instances":[{"className":"IsTotal","name":"FieldSpecification.instIsTotalCrAnFieldOpNormalOrderRel","typeNames":["FieldSpecification.CrAnFieldOp","FieldSpecification.normalOrderRel"]},{"className":"IsTrans","name":"FieldSpecification.instIsTransCrAnFieldOpNormalOrderRel","typeNames":["FieldSpecification.CrAnFieldOp","FieldSpecification.normalOrderRel"]},{"className":"Decidable","name":"FieldSpecification.instDecidableNormalOrderRel","typeNames":["FieldSpecification.normalOrderRel"]}],"name":"PhysLean.QFT.PerturbationTheory.FieldSpecification.NormalOrder"}